    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Gagea subalpina are respiratory issues, such as bronchitis, through the expectorant properties of its alkaloids, particularly gageamin. This plant has been used to treat various skin conditions, like eczema, due to its anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties. Additionally, Gagea subalpina has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, making it effective in treating urinary tract infections. Its anti-inflammatory properties also make it a potential treatment for arthritis, reducing joint pain and inflammation. Gagea subalpina's antioxidant properties have been shown to protect against oxidative stress, which can lead to conditions like cancer and Alzheimer's disease.",
