    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Gagea subalpina are its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial activities. The anti-inflammatory properties of Gagea subalpina are attributed to the presence of flavonoids, such as kaempferol and quercetin, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. The antioxidant properties of this plant are due to the presence of saponins, which can scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Additionally, Gagea subalpina's antimicrobial properties are attributed to the presence of volatile oils, such as borneol and bornyl acetate, which have been shown to exhibit antibacterial and antifungal activities. The anti-cancer properties of Gagea subalpina are also attributed to the presence of terpenoids, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of cancer cells and induce apoptosis.",
